cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as speech recognition and text-to-speech systems. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper specifically focuses on grapheme-to-phoneme conversion, which is related to speech processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a machine learning method for G2P conversion using token-level ensemble distillation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing an AI model for G2P conversion. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category as the paper does not seem to directly relate to social or information networks.
